{"word":"ἀμενηνός","slug":"ἀμενηνός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀμενηνός</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:μένος'><el>μένος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>powerless, fleeting, feeble</i>, of ghosts, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; of dreams, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; of one wounded, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of mortal men generally, <b>Hhymn.</b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}